Included with the Mididuino editor is the source code for all the published firmwares, as well as the source code of all the tutorials described in this document. To open one of these files, select it in File -> Examples. Once the file is opened, you can compile it by pressing the \'93Play\'94 button (or Apple-R on Macosx or Ctrl-R on windows/linux). Once the firmware compiles fine (errors are shown in the lower log part of the editor), the firmware can be uploaded by pressing \'93Upload\'94 button (arrow to the right, or Apple-U / Ctrl-U). This will transmit the firmware over MIDI like the Patch Manager does. The device should switch into the bootloader mode. If it doesn\'92t, it can manually be put into the bootloader mode by holding the topright button down while switching the device on.}